snippet.textDisplay: The first computer my family had was a 486DX @ 33MHz. This was a high end machine. It had a VESA video card with 1MB of VRAM and 8MB of DRAM. We dropped about $4200 in 1991, so just a little shy of $8000 in today's dollars. (My stepdad was a database programmer for a major US city).... Funny thing? The AMD Threadripper 3990X has more L3 CACHE, than the $1200 250MB Caviar hard drive in my system from thirty years ago. Golly. I can't wait to spin up 10,000 DOSBOX VMs on this and play Wolfenstien 3D on all of them 😎😆
